{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17600955","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17600955"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T12:08:42+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T12:08:42+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15639"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15639","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15639"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.16,0.16,0.47,0.16,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8330"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71021"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8330","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8330"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15639"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56492"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"7607"},{"type":"tags","id":"10075"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20095"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20099"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71021","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/71021"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA newborn presents with ambiguous genitalia, salt-wasting crisis, and very low levels of all steroid hormones including cortisol, aldosterone, and sex steroids. Genetic testing reveals a mutation affecting the first enzymatic step of steroid hormone synthesis.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following enzymes is most likely deficient in this patient?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Side-chain cleavage enzyme","3-beta hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase","21-hydroxylase","11-beta hydroxylase","Aldosterone synthase"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient\u0027s presentation is consistent with \u003Cstrong\u003Eside-chain cleavage enzyme\u003C/strong\u003E (P450scc) deficiency. As this enzyme catalyzes the first step in steroid hormone synthesis, its absence results in deficiency of all steroid hormones.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other enzymes act later in the pathway:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E3-beta hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase\u003C/strong\u003E deficiency would still allow some pregnenolone production\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E21-hydroxylase\u003C/strong\u003E deficiency is the most common cause of congenital adrenal hyperplasia but allows production of androgens\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E11-beta hydroxylase\u003C/strong\u003E deficiency causes mineralocorticoid excess and androgen excess\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAldosterone synthase\u003C/strong\u003E deficiency only affects mineralocorticoid production\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe complete absence of all steroid hormones points to a block at the first enzymatic step, which is the conversion of cholesterol to pregnenolone by P450scc.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Cholesterol side-chain cleavage enzyme (P450scc) catalyzes the first and rate-limiting step in steroid hormone synthesis.","The conversion of cholesterol to pregnenolone occurs in mitochondria and requires three chemical reactions.","Deficiency of P450scc enzyme causes severe congenital adrenal insufficiency"],"references":["Katsumata N. Cholesterol Side-Chain Cleavage Enzyme (SCC) Deficiency. Clin Pediatr Endocrinol. 2007;16(3):63-8. doi: 10.1297/cpe.16.63. Epub 2007 Aug 8. PMID: 24790347; PMCID: PMC4004890.","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine System: Netter Collection of Medical Illustrations: Endocrine System E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Wass, J. A., \u0026 Stewart, P. M. (Eds.). (2011). Oxford textbook of endocrinology and diabetes. Oxford University Press, USA"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56492"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15639"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56492","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56492"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-16T18:56:30+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-16T18:57:35+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8330"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71021"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},